WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:05.150
Ah oui. with my life. Monsieur.

2
00:00:03.967 --> 00:00:05.599
- S'il vous plaît.
- Oui.

3
00:00:05.900 --> 00:00:10.050
I like you.

4
00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:11.615
Thank you.

5
00:00:13.318 --> 00:00:14.104
"Bon" chance.

6
00:00:17.432 --> 00:00:18.542
<i>Bonne</i> chance.

7
00:00:26.099 --> 00:00:31.149
OK. so... How would you like some champagne?

8
00:00:32.099 --> 00:00:35.598
How'd that get in there?

9
00:00:35.599 --> 00:00:40.649
Aw. don't cry.

10
00:00:45.199 --> 00:00:50.749
- Look at you. Wow! Beautiful.
- Thanks.

11
00:00:52.999 --> 00:00:55.698
Is this place in your budget?

12
00:00:55.699 --> 00:00:57.598
Oh. it's a special occasion.

13
00:00:57.599 --> 00:01:00.598
You're on Broadway.

14
00:01:00.599 --> 00:01:02.798
I don't feel like much of a star tonight.

15
00:01:02.799 --> 00:01:04.298
Well. you are a star.

16
00:01:04.299 --> 00:01:09.049
And you've earned it.

17
00:01:09.399 --> 00:01:11.497
Peter. you have no idea how I feel right now.

18
00:01:11.498 --> 00:01:15.097
Oh no. I know exactly how you feel.

19
00:01:15.098 --> 00:01:15.897
Listen.

20
00:01:15.898 --> 00:01:17.497
I have been through this.

21
00:01:17.498 --> 00:01:19.097
Happens to me all the time.

22
00:01:19.098 --> 00:01:22.097
I see Spider Man posters in the window.

23
00:01:22.098 --> 00:01:24.197
Kids running around with me on their sweaters.

24
00:01:24.198 --> 00:01:25.897
Big Halloween item.

25
00:01:25.898 --> 00:01:28.597
I don't know. I guess I've become something of an icon.

26
00:01:28.598 --> 00:01:30.397
Like yesterday.

27
00:01:30.398 --> 00:01:34.497
They keep screaming: "Spider-Man! Spider-Man!"

28
00:01:34.498 --> 00:01:36.297
I don't know. I mean.

29
00:01:36.298 --> 00:01:38.197
I'm thinking to myself.

30
00:01:38.198 --> 00:01:44.397
"I'm just a nerdy kid from Queens. Do I deserve this?"

31
00:01:44.398 --> 00:01:49.848
- Hi. Pete.
- Hi.

32
00:01:54.898 --> 00:01:57.896
Hi. My parents and I are just having dinner here.

33
00:01:57.897 --> 00:01:58.896
Hello.

34
00:01:58.897 --> 00:02:00.696
I'm Gwen Stacey.

35
00:02:00.697 --> 00:02:04.496
This is Mary Jane Watson.

36
00:02:04.497 --> 00:02:10.496
Oh. it's so nice to finally meet you. 
Pete talks about you all the time.

37
00:02:10.497 --> 00:02:14.496
Gwen is my lab partner in Dr Connor's class.

38
00:02:14.497 --> 00:02:17.596
Pete's something of a genius. 
I'd be completely lost without him.

39
00:02:17.597 --> 00:02:19.896
Which actually reminds me--

40
00:02:19.897 --> 00:02:23.596
Pete. if you got a picture of my kiss with Spider-Man.

41
00:02:23.597 --> 00:02:25.496
could you bring it to class?

42
00:02:25.497 --> 00:02:27.396
I'd really love it.

43
00:02:27.397 --> 00:02:30.096
For my portfolio.

44
00:02:30.097 --> 00:02:33.696
After all. who gets kissed by Spider-Man. right?

45
00:02:33.697 --> 00:02:36.696
I can't imagine.

46
00:02:36.697 --> 00:02:40.496
Well. it was lovely to meet you.

47
00:02:40.497 --> 00:02:45.447
- Good night.
- Good night.

48
00:02:52.496 --> 00:02:59.895
Uh. she's in my science class. It's not her best subject.

49
00:02:59.896 --> 00:03:01.095
What?

50
00:03:01.096 --> 00:03:04.595
How come you never mentioned her?

51
00:03:04.596 --> 00:03:07.095
She's your lab partner.

52
00:03:07.096 --> 00:03:09.395
you saved her life.

53
00:03:09.396 --> 00:03:14.395
she thinks you're a genius and she had her 
polished fingernails all over you?

54
00:03:14.396 --> 00:03:17.595
Or didn't you notice?

55
00:03:17.596 --> 00:03:21.895
And she gave Spider-Man the key to the city.

56
00:03:21.896 --> 00:03:26.446
I'll never forget that.

57
00:03:27.596 --> 00:03:31.195
- She's just a girl in my class.
- Let me ask you something.

58
00:03:31.196 --> 00:03:33.294
When you kissed her.

59
00:03:33.295 --> 00:03:35.794
who was kissing her?

60
00:03:35.795 --> 00:03:38.694
Spider-Man or Peter?

61
00:03:38.695 --> 00:03:41.794
- What do you mean?
- You know exactly what I mean.

62
00:03:41.795 --> 00:03:44.294
That was our kiss.

63
00:03:44.295 --> 00:03:46.794
Why would you do that?

64
00:03:46.795 --> 00:03:49.994
You must have known how it made me feel.

65
00:03:49.995 --> 00:03:52.094
Do you want to push me away?

66
00:03:52.095 --> 00:03:54.094
Push you away?

67
00:03:54.095 --> 00:03:56.994
Why would I want to push you away? I love you.

68
00:03:56.995 --> 00:04:02.294
You're my girlfriend. She's a girl in my class. MJ.

69
00:04:02.295 --> 00:04:07.294
I don't feel very well. I'm sorry. I have to go.

70
00:04:07.295 --> 00:04:12.345
- Where are you going?
- Please don't follow me.

71
00:04:13.395 --> 00:04:18.145
Here we are.

72
00:04:51.394 --> 00:04:55.893
<i>Hi. it's MJ. Sing a song at the beep. Beep!</i>

73
00:04:55.894 --> 00:04:59.993
Hello. Uh...

74
00:04:59.994 --> 00:05:01.893
I wish you'd pick up the phone.

75
00:05:01.894 --> 00:05:04.393
I don't know what's going on.

76
00:05:04.394 --> 00:05:07.592
I don't know if you got the messages. or what.

77
00:05:07.593 --> 00:05:09.792
But...

78
00:05:09.793 --> 00:05:13.792
I just want to talk to you.

79
00:05:13.793 --> 00:05:19.043
OK. Call me. all right?

80
00:05:27.393 --> 00:05:29.092
- Hallo?
- Mr Parker?

81
00:05:29.093 --> 00:05:31.692
- Yeah?
- This is Detective Neil Garett from the 2nd precinct.

82
00:05:31.693 --> 00:05:35.092
I'm calling on behalf of Captain Stacey.

83
00:05:35.093 --> 00:05:37.192
He would like you to come down to the station to speak with him.

84
00:05:37.193 --> 00:05:39.992
Originally we thought that this man. Dennis Carradine.

85
00:05:39.993 --> 00:05:43.292
was your husband's killer.

86
00:05:43.293 --> 00:05:45.692
We were wrong.

87
00:05:45.693 --> 00:05:49.692
- What?
- Turns out Mr Carradine was only an accomplice.

88
00:05:49.693 --> 00:05:52.292
The actual killer is still at large.

89
00:05:52.293 --> 00:05:53.991
What are you talking about?

90
00:05:53.992 --> 00:05:59.642
This is the man who killed your husband.

91
00:06:01.392 --> 00:06:05.891
His name is Flint Marko.
He's a small-time crook who's been in and out of prison.

92
00:06:05.892 --> 00:06:07.291
You got this wrong.

93
00:06:07.292 --> 00:06:09.791
Two days ago. he escaped.

94
00:06:09.792 --> 00:06:12.291
Evidently. he confessed his guilt to a cellmate.

95
00:06:12.292 --> 00:06:18.442
And we have a couple of witnesses who corroborate the story.

96
00:06:28.692 --> 00:06:33.642
No. wait. sir. You don't want to do this.

97
00:06:44.391 --> 00:06:50.241
Get in! What are you doing?

98
00:07:06.091 --> 00:07:07.790
Would you put these photos away. please?

99
00:07:07.791 --> 00:07:10.890
I'm sorry. Mrs Parker. I know this isn't easy.

100
00:07:10.891 --> 00:07:12.990
but please be patient with us.

101
00:07:12.991 --> 00:07:15.290
We're doing our job. We will catch him.

102
00:07:15.291 --> 00:07:16.690
No. you're not doing your job.

103
00:07:16.691 --> 00:07:18.190
I watched my uncle die.

104
00:07:18.191 --> 00:07:19.690
We chased down the wrong man.

105
00:07:19.691 --> 00:07:22.590
Now you're telling me there's suspicions for two years? Witnesses?

106
00:07:22.591 --> 00:07:25.890
- Why weren't we told about this?
- Settle down. sir.

107
00:07:25.891 --> 00:07:28.389
-No. I have no intention of settling down!
This man killed my uncle.

108
00:07:28.390 --> 00:07:32.840
and he's still out there!

109
00:07:39.090 --> 00:07:43.689
L-20 Parkway. all officers in the vicinity please report.

110
00:07:43.690 --> 00:07:49.940
We have an abandoned vehicle and an abandoned man in the middle of the street.

111
00:07:49.941 --> 00:07:50.941
Sorry. Wabash Avenue.

112
00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:55.889
Peter. it's MJ.

113
00:07:55.890 --> 00:08:01.940
I'm not here about what happened at dinner. Just please open up.

114
00:08:06.590 --> 00:08:09.089
Aunt May called me. She told me about what happened.

115
00:08:09.090 --> 00:08:11.289
She's worried about you.

116
00:08:11.290 --> 00:08:12.789
I'm worried about you.

117
00:08:12.790 --> 00:08:15.288
Don't be. I'm fine.

118
00:08:15.289 --> 00:08:17.188
I don't want you to do something stupid.

119
00:08:17.189 --> 00:08:19.988
Like try to find my uncle's killer?

120
00:08:19.989 --> 00:08:22.488
And do something you'll regret.

121
00:08:22.489 --> 00:08:24.288
Like...

122
00:08:24.289 --> 00:08:25.688
with that other guy.

123
00:08:25.689 --> 00:08:27.288
He had a gun on me.

124
00:08:27.289 --> 00:08:30.988
- I made a move. and he fell. I told you that.
- I'm not accusing you of anything.

125
00:08:30.989 --> 00:08:37.139
<i>C-22. auto at 566. 9th Avenue...</i>
- Will you turn that thing off?

126
00:08:41.989 --> 00:08:45.488
Peter. I'm here because I care about you.

127
00:08:45.489 --> 00:08:51.088
And I know that you made a mistake and that you feel guilty. but--

128
00:08:51.089 --> 00:08:54.288
- I want to be here for you.
- OK.

129
00:08:54.289 --> 00:08:56.288
I get it. Thank you.

130
00:08:56.289 --> 00:08:58.888
But. uh. I'm fine.

131
00:08:58.889 --> 00:09:03.139
I don't need your help.

132
00:09:08.288 --> 00:09:11.187
Everybody needs help sometimes. Peter.

133
00:09:11.188 --> 00:09:15.738
Even Spider-Man.

134
00:09:21.790 --> 00:09:23.652
<i>90 - X-ray - 98.</i>

135
00:09:26.433 --> 00:09:30.144
<i>10-31 at 642. Madison Av...</i>

136
00:09:30.810 --> 00:09:34.639
<i>1-3-Tom has responded 10-20 at 540. East 107...</i>

137
00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:39.120
<i>male *** inside apartment B on first floor...</i>

138
00:09:43.394 --> 00:09:46.372
<i>310-11 of a residence. 738...</i>

139
00:10:47.486 --> 00:10:49.485
- Don't hurt me! Just give me a chance!
- What about my uncle?

140
00:10:49.486 --> 00:10:50.985
Did you give him a chance?

141
00:10:50.986 --> 00:10:55.636
Did you?

142
00:11:05.086 --> 00:11:09.336
Where am I?

143
00:11:23.185 --> 00:11:26.884
What is this?

144
00:11:26.885 --> 00:11:31.384
I feel...

145
00:11:31.385 --> 00:11:32.984
Wow.

146
00:11:32.985 --> 00:11:37.735
This feels good.

147
00:12:05.485 --> 00:12:09.183
This is something else.

148
00:12:09.184 --> 00:12:10.183
What do you think?

149
00:12:10.184 --> 00:12:12.683
I've never seen anything like it.

150
00:12:12.684 --> 00:12:15.483
I'm a physicist. not a biologist. but...

151
00:12:15.484 --> 00:12:21.134
- I'll look at it in the morning. run some tests.
- Can we do that now?

152
00:12:23.784 --> 00:12:28.134
It seems to like you.

153
00:12:28.484 --> 00:12:31.083
-Don't let any of that get on you.
- Why not?

154
00:12:31.084 --> 00:12:33.583
It has the characteristics of a symbiote.

155
00:12:33.584 --> 00:12:37.183
which needs to bond to a host to survive.

156
00:12:37.184 --> 00:12:41.183
And sometimes. these things in nature. when they bind.

157
00:12:41.184 --> 00:12:44.883
they can be hard to unbind.

158
00:12:44.884 --> 00:12:48.483
[female voice over radio]
<i>Bank robbery in progress. First Eastern Bank at ** Bismarck.</i>

159
00:12:48.484 --> 00:12:52.983
<i>Another sand storm is reported in the vicinity. 
All cars. proceed with caution.</i>

160
00:12:52.984 --> 00:12:57.334
Marko.

161
00:13:49.682 --> 00:13:52.081
Buddy. love the new outfit.

162
00:13:52.082 --> 00:13:57.381
This is exactly what I need to scoop. partner. 
Give me some of that web action.

163
00:13:57.382 --> 00:14:00.681
See you. chum.

164
00:14:00.682 --> 00:14:05.232
What the hell?

165
00:14:44.881 --> 00:14:48.880
Flint Marko?

166
00:14:48.881 --> 00:14:50.180
What do you want from me?

167
00:14:50.181 --> 00:14:52.580
Remember Ben Parker?

168
00:14:52.581 --> 00:14:57.080
The old man you shot down in cold blood?

169
00:14:57.081 --> 00:15:00.680
What does it matter to you anyway?

170
00:15:00.681 --> 00:15:05.331
Everything!

171
00:15:39.780 --> 00:15:44.430
It's time to pay. Marko.

172
00:16:21.779 --> 00:16:26.529
Good riddance.

173
00:16:44.179 --> 00:16:45.263
Re-ent!

174
00:16:45.264 --> 00:16:46.278
Not now.

175
00:16:46.279 --> 00:16:50.277
This is a free country. It's not a rent-free country.

176
00:16:50.278 --> 00:16:51.312
Leave me alone.

177
00:16:51.313 --> 00:16:52.277
Give me rent.

178
00:16:52.278 --> 00:16:57.528
You'll get your rent when you fix this damn door!

179
00:17:07.278 --> 00:17:08.912
That wasn't cool.

180
00:17:08.913 --> 00:17:13.728
He is good boy.

181
00:17:15.478 --> 00:17:19.928
He must be in some kind of trouble.

182
00:18:05.577 --> 00:18:08.576
Flint Marko. the man who killed uncle Ben--

183
00:18:08.577 --> 00:18:11.576
he was killed last night.

184
00:18:11.577 --> 00:18:14.376
O my--

185
00:18:14.377 --> 00:18:15.376
What happened?

186
00:18:15.377 --> 00:18:19.076
Spider-Man killed him.

187
00:18:19.077 --> 00:18:20.211
Spider-Man?

188
00:18:20.212 --> 00:18:23.276
I don't understand.

189
00:18:23.277 --> 00:18:27.526
Spider-Man doesn't kill people.

190
00:18:28.276 --> 00:18:32.526
What happened?

191
00:18:37.276 --> 00:18:41.526
I... He was...

192
00:18:43.276 --> 00:18:47.975
I thought that you'd feel...

193
00:18:47.976 --> 00:18:50.975
He deserved it. didn't he?

194
00:18:50.976 --> 00:18:57.226
I don't think it's for us to say whether a person deserves to live or die.

195
00:18:57.276 --> 00:19:01.275
Aunt May. he killed uncle Ben.

196
00:19:01.276 --> 00:19:03.775
Uncle Ben meant the world to us.

197
00:19:03.776 --> 00:19:10.026
But he wouldn't want us living one second with revenge in our hearts.

198
00:19:11.475 --> 00:19:14.774
It's like a poison.

199
00:19:14.775 --> 00:19:18.874
It can take you over.

200
00:19:18.875 --> 00:19:21.274
Before you know it.

201
00:19:21.275 --> 00:19:26.125
turn us into something ugly.

202
00:20:25.074 --> 00:20:26.573
Hello.

203
00:20:26.574 --> 00:20:28.673
Hey. Harry. it's MJ.

204
00:20:28.674 --> 00:20:31.073
-Hi.
- I need some company.

205
00:20:31.074 --> 00:20:33.773
Are you doing anything? Can I stop by?

206
00:20:33.774 --> 00:20:35.773
Yeah. sure. Come on over.

207
00:20:35.774 --> 00:20:38.073
OK. Are you sure it's OK?

208
00:20:38.074 --> 00:20:40.073
I'm not doing anything.

209
00:20:40.074 --> 00:20:41.273
Please. come over.

210
00:20:41.274 --> 00:20:42.473
OK. I'll see you soon.

211
00:20:42.474 --> 00:20:46.272
-Great.
- Bye.

212
00:20:46.273 --> 00:20:48.672
-Bernard?
- Yes. Mr Osborn?

213
00:20:48.673 --> 00:20:51.172
We're having a guest. Can you get some food?

214
00:20:51.173 --> 00:20:54.172
- A guest!?
- Yeah. a guest.

215
00:20:54.173 --> 00:20:55.472
-A guest <i>guest</i>?

216
00:20:55.473 --> 00:20:57.072
Will you just get some food?

217
00:20:57.073 --> 00:21:01.323
Rightaway. Sir.

218
00:21:16.773 --> 00:21:19.072
Hey. Mr Ditkovitch.

219
00:21:19.073 --> 00:21:20.772
An orange?

220
00:21:20.773 --> 00:21:21.872
No. thanks.

221
00:21:21.873 --> 00:21:23.572
Listen--

222
00:21:23.573 --> 00:21:25.972
I'm really sorry for what happened earlier.

223
00:21:25.973 --> 00:21:29.172
I shouldn't have yelled about that door. 
It was nothing to be angry about.

224
00:21:29.173 --> 00:21:31.872
Ah. it's not big deal.

225
00:21:31.873 --> 00:21:33.771
But if you feel that bad about it.

226
00:21:33.772 --> 00:21:36.171
you can buy me pizza some time.

227
00:21:36.172 --> 00:21:38.071
Today's good.

228
00:21:38.072 --> 00:21:39.071
OK.

229
00:21:39.072 --> 00:21:40.371
Have problem with the phone?

230
00:21:40.372 --> 00:21:44.171
No. no. I was just-- was trying to figure out what to say.

231
00:21:44.172 --> 00:21:46.671
If it's a woman you're calling.

232
00:21:46.672 --> 00:21:49.571
then you say: "You're a good woman.

233
00:21:49.572 --> 00:21:54.222
"I'm good man."

234
00:21:56.972 --> 00:21:58.771
- Hi. Pete.
- Hi.

235
00:21:58.772 --> 00:22:01.371
- He's calling a woman.
- Are you calling Mary Jane?

236
00:22:01.372 --> 00:22:04.071
- I think that would be so good...
- It's none of your business.

237
00:22:04.072 --> 00:22:07.871
Go! Go.

238
00:22:07.872 --> 00:22:12.822
- Give her a call.
- Thanks.

239
00:22:13.072 --> 00:22:17.522
- Bye.
- Bye.

240
00:22:33.171 --> 00:22:35.070
You hungry?

241
00:22:35.071 --> 00:22:36.670
Yeah.

242
00:22:36.671 --> 00:22:41.021
Come in.

243
00:22:42.571 --> 00:22:46.921
Hope you like peppers.

244
00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:13.220
I love 'em.

245
00:23:22.070 --> 00:23:26.320
Oh. the butter!

246
00:23:49.170 --> 00:23:52.868
Well. we can use that part.

247
00:23:52.869 --> 00:23:55.268
"You've been dreaming."

248
00:23:55.269 --> 00:23:59.968
"Nothing like a little self-deception to get you through the night."

249
00:23:59.969 --> 00:24:01.568
- All right.
- When did you write that?

250
00:24:01.569 --> 00:24:04.368
- 12th grade.
- It's intense.

251
00:24:04.369 --> 00:24:06.568
So. do you want the part?

252
00:24:06.569 --> 00:24:11.319
- I'd love to be in your play.
- Cheers.

253
00:24:11.869 --> 00:24:16.668
You know. there's not even a scar.

254
00:24:16.669 --> 00:24:21.119
Barely.

255
00:24:35.969 --> 00:24:37.768
- Sorry.
- Me too.

256
00:24:37.769 --> 00:24:40.667
- I didn't mean to do that.
- No. it's OK. Please.

257
00:24:40.668 --> 00:24:42.867
Forgive me.

258
00:24:42.868 --> 00:24:45.967
Mary Jane.

259
00:24:45.968 --> 00:24:48.367
Mary Jane.

260
00:24:48.368 --> 00:24:53.418
- Mary Jane. please!
- I'm sorry.

261
00:25:04.968 --> 00:25:10.818
You've taken your eye off the ball.

262
00:25:29.067 --> 00:25:33.517
What have you done?

263
00:25:33.514 --> 00:25:35.059
Avenge me!

264
00:25:37.867 --> 00:25:41.366
My father-- he died. right?

265
00:25:41.367 --> 00:25:42.166
Yeah.

266
00:25:42.167 --> 00:25:44.166
Just wish that I could remember more about him.

267
00:25:44.167 --> 00:25:45.566
Well. he loved you.

268
00:25:45.567 --> 00:25:47.266
That's the main thing.

269
00:25:47.267 --> 00:25:51.466
<i>I swear on my father's grave: Spider-Man will pay.</i>

270
00:25:51.467 --> 00:25:54.866
Harry.

271
00:25:54.867 --> 00:25:58.766
Remember me?

272
00:25:58.767 --> 00:26:00.766
Yes. father.

273
00:26:00.767 --> 00:26:01.766
I remember.

274
00:26:01.767 --> 00:26:03.466
I was right about her.

275
00:26:03.467 --> 00:26:04.966
about Peter.

276
00:26:04.967 --> 00:26:08.666
about everything.

277
00:26:08.667 --> 00:26:11.366
<i>You know what you must do.</i>

278
00:26:11.367 --> 00:26:14.865
<i>Make him suffer. Make him wish he were dead.</i>

279
00:26:14.866 --> 00:26:21.416
<i>First. we attack his heart.</i>

280
00:26:29.466 --> 00:26:32.565
[Answering machine starts]
"Hi. it's me. Sing your song at the beep."

281
00:26:32.566 --> 00:26:33.665
<i>Hey. MJ.</i>

282
00:26:33.666 --> 00:26:37.365
<i>It's Peter.</i>

283
00:26:37.366 --> 00:26:41.165
<i>I want to talk to you about last night.</i>

284
00:26:41.166 --> 00:26:43.165
<i>I don't know what I was thinking.</i>

285
00:26:43.166 --> 00:26:45.765
<i>I know you were just there to help. and--</i>

286
00:26:45.766 --> 00:26:53.416
<i>I. uh-- I don't know. I want to see you.</i>

287
00:26:55.666 --> 00:26:57.565
If you want Peter to live.

288
00:26:57.566 --> 00:27:02.116
you're gonna do something for me.

289
00:27:03.765 --> 00:27:05.264
- Yeah?
- It's Ursula.

290
00:27:05.265 --> 00:27:09.615
Come in.

291
00:27:15.765 --> 00:27:17.964
-Hi. Pete.
- Hi.

292
00:27:17.965 --> 00:27:21.464
There's a phone call for you.

293
00:27:21.465 --> 00:27:23.164
It's Mary Jane. she called back!

294
00:27:23.165 --> 00:27:26.964
-Really?
- Yeah!

295
00:27:26.965 --> 00:27:29.164
I put the phone on top of the thing.

296
00:27:29.165 --> 00:27:33.515
Thanks. OK.

297
00:27:34.708 --> 00:27:35.969
-Hey.
- Hi.

298
00:27:36.004 --> 00:27:37.764
I was so glad you called.

299
00:27:37.765 --> 00:27:40.864
-I've been-- trying to--
- Can you meet me?

300
00:27:40.865 --> 00:27:43.164
-You bet.
- Now?

301
00:27:43.165 --> 00:27:44.564
OK. Where?

302
00:27:44.565 --> 00:27:46.564
At the bridge. in the park.

303
00:27:46.565 --> 00:27:48.163
On my way.

304
00:27:48.164 --> 00:27:53.114
Hey...love you...

305
00:28:10.464 --> 00:28:14.714
You look beautiful.

306
00:28:14.715 --> 00:28:15.715
Peonies.

307
00:28:17.964 --> 00:28:19.163
You OK?

308
00:28:19.164 --> 00:28:21.263
No.

309
00:28:21.264 --> 00:28:26.314
-There's something I have to tell you. Pete.
- OK.

310
00:28:26.464 --> 00:28:29.363
It's not working.

311
00:28:29.364 --> 00:28:32.063
You and me.

312
00:28:32.064 --> 00:28:33.863
What?

313
00:28:33.864 --> 00:28:36.862
I don't want to see you anymore.

314
00:28:36.863 --> 00:28:38.762
What are you talking about?

315
00:28:38.763 --> 00:28:43.462
I don't know.

316
00:28:43.463 --> 00:28:49.662
I'm lonely.
You aren't there for me.

317
00:28:49.663 --> 00:28:52.662
I can't do this.

318
00:28:52.663 --> 00:28:54.562
-It's over.
- No. Please.

319
00:28:54.563 --> 00:28:58.562
Please don't say that.

320
00:28:58.563 --> 00:29:00.362
I know. I've been selfish.

321
00:29:00.363 --> 00:29:02.962
-But I can do better. I can change.
- It's not that simple.

322
00:29:02.963 --> 00:29:05.462
We love each other! I love you!

323
00:29:05.463 --> 00:29:07.462
And we have problems. When people have problems. they work it out.

324
00:29:07.463 --> 00:29:12.513
They talk to each other.

325
00:29:15.763 --> 00:29:18.462
Look. you see?

326
00:29:18.463 --> 00:29:21.761
You know what this is?

327
00:29:21.762 --> 00:29:25.061
-You know what I want for us?
- There's someone else.

328
00:29:25.062 --> 00:29:29.912
I've fallen in love with someone else.

329
00:30:01.162 --> 00:30:02.861
She says that she's lonely.

330
00:30:02.862 --> 00:30:06.861
and that I'm not there for her.

331
00:30:06.862 --> 00:30:11.512
There's another guy.

332
00:30:12.161 --> 00:30:14.760
How are you holding up?

333
00:30:14.761 --> 00:30:18.460
Not good.

334
00:30:18.461 --> 00:30:22.060
Harry. I was going to propose to her.

335
00:30:22.061 --> 00:30:25.860
Really?

336
00:30:25.861 --> 00:30:28.560
She's been going through a tough time lately.

337
00:30:28.561 --> 00:30:29.760
Career.

338
00:30:29.761 --> 00:30:32.760
I mean. a singing waitress at a jazz club--

339
00:30:32.761 --> 00:30:36.060
that's not exactly what she had in mind for herself.

340
00:30:36.061 --> 00:30:39.460
A singing waitress? What are you talking about?

341
00:30:39.461 --> 00:30:42.260
She was fired from the show.

342
00:30:42.261 --> 00:30:44.260
Didn't she tell you?

343
00:30:44.261 --> 00:30:47.260
She was fired?

344
00:30:47.261 --> 00:30:50.360
She was fired and she told you?

345
00:30:50.361 --> 00:30:54.060
She didn't tell me?

346
00:30:54.061 --> 00:30:57.859
That's why I asked you here. Pete.

347
00:30:57.860 --> 00:31:01.659
I'm the other guy.

348
00:31:01.660 --> 00:31:03.559
What?

349
00:31:03.560 --> 00:31:06.759
Look. she came to me one afternoon. troubled.

350
00:31:06.760 --> 00:31:10.359
She needed someone. and I was there for her.

351
00:31:10.360 --> 00:31:12.459
I've always loved her. Pete.

352
00:31:12.460 --> 00:31:13.659
You know that.

353
00:31:13.660 --> 00:31:15.159
It just...

354
00:31:15.160 --> 00:31:20.010
started.

355
00:31:25.160 --> 00:31:27.159
I don't believe this.

356
00:31:27.160 --> 00:31:28.759
I don't believe you.

357
00:31:28.760 --> 00:31:32.759
I'm really sorry.

358
00:31:32.760 --> 00:31:37.010
I just thought you should know.

359
00:31:43.159 --> 00:31:44.458
Can I warm you up?

360
00:31:44.459 --> 00:31:48.058
Yes. please.

361
00:31:48.059 --> 00:31:50.658
How's the pie?

362
00:31:50.659 --> 00:31:54.809
So good.

363
00:32:55.558 --> 00:32:59.808
Would you like a drink?

364
00:32:59.958 --> 00:33:01.457
I'm sorry.

365
00:33:01.458 --> 00:33:05.257
What was I thinking? 
Bad for the public image. right. Mr Key-to-the-city?

366
00:33:05.258 --> 00:33:08.957
What did you do to her?

367
00:33:08.958 --> 00:33:10.457
I did what you failed to do.

368
00:33:10.458 --> 00:33:12.457
I was there for her.

369
00:33:12.458 --> 00:33:14.657
Mary Jane and I. we understand each other.

370
00:33:14.658 --> 00:33:16.257
She doesn't know what you are.

371
00:33:16.258 --> 00:33:20.056
Peter. She knows me very well.

372
00:33:20.057 --> 00:33:21.356
And when she kissed me.

373
00:33:21.357 --> 00:33:24.656
it was just like she used to kiss me.

374
00:33:24.657 --> 00:33:27.956
That taste.

375
00:33:27.957 --> 00:33:32.407
Strawberries.

376
00:34:04.856 --> 00:34:09.206
How d'ya like that. Spidey?

377
00:34:09.956 --> 00:34:14.206
That all you got?

378
00:34:18.656 --> 00:34:19.855
Stinks. doesn't it?

379
00:34:19.856 --> 00:34:26.106
I protected you in high school. 
Now I'm gonna kick your little ass.

380
00:35:10.955 --> 00:35:13.454
You gonna kill me like you killed my father?

381
00:35:13.455 --> 00:35:15.854
I'm done trying to convince you.

382
00:35:15.855 --> 00:35:18.154
You took him from me.

383
00:35:18.155 --> 00:35:19.754
He loved me.

384
00:35:19.755 --> 00:35:21.054
No.

385
00:35:21.055 --> 00:35:23.754
he despised you.

386
00:35:23.755 --> 00:35:28.405
You were an embarrassment for him.

387
00:35:29.355 --> 00:35:32.754
Look at that little Goblin junior.

388
00:35:32.755 --> 00:35:37.105
Gonna cry?

389
00:36:09.954 --> 00:36:12.253
HEADLINES: "THIEF! Spider-Man shows his true colors"
<i>- Spider-Man used to make me feel safe.</i>

390
00:36:12.254 --> 00:36:14.453
<i>Now I'm afraid to walk home from work.</i>

391
00:36:14.454 --> 00:36:16.453
My son thought the world of this guy.

392
00:36:16.454 --> 00:36:18.653
I have a 9 year old daughter. loves Spider-Man.

393
00:36:18.654 --> 00:36:20.353
Who's she supposed to look up to now?

394
00:36:20.354 --> 00:36:23.253
This is the guy they gave the key to the city to?

395
00:36:23.254 --> 00:36:28.052
"I'm gonna put some dirt in your eye."

396
00:36:28.053 --> 00:36:31.652
-Cheers! New staff photographer!
- I just got lucky.

397
00:36:31.653 --> 00:36:33.052
This is so wonderful for you.

398
00:36:33.053 --> 00:36:39.203
Well. you might wanna tell JJ to make a little more wall space.

399
00:36:42.053 --> 00:36:45.652
-Good morning.
- It's a beautiful day. huh?

400
00:36:45.653 --> 00:36:48.852
What was it you said. I'll never get that picture?

401
00:36:48.853 --> 00:36:52.052
There's your hero.

402
00:36:52.053 --> 00:36:53.952
I never thought he'd really do that.

403
00:36:53.953 --> 00:36:55.652
See? Right there.

404
00:36:55.653 --> 00:36:57.052
you made a judgment call.

405
00:36:57.053 --> 00:36:58.652
You gotta see it as it is.

406
00:36:58.653 --> 00:37:00.252
It's funny you should say that.

407
00:37:00.253 --> 00:37:02.152
'cause I was looking through some old photos. and

408
00:37:02.153 --> 00:37:08.603
looks very. uh-- similar.

409
00:37:08.853 --> 00:37:11.651
OK-- Well. I gotta get back to work.

410
00:37:11.652 --> 00:37:13.151
You're trash. Brock.

411
00:37:13.152 --> 00:37:14.751
Excuse me?

412
00:37:14.752 --> 00:37:19.202
Your picture is a fake.

413
00:37:19.452 --> 00:37:21.651
Parker. you are such a boy scout.

414
00:37:21.652 --> 00:37:25.951
When are you gonna give a guy a break?

415
00:37:25.952 --> 00:37:28.051
You want forgiveness?

416
00:37:28.052 --> 00:37:29.751
Get religion.

417
00:37:29.752 --> 00:37:34.202
-What's going on here?
- Are you guys all right?

418
00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:39.151
Yeah. no. we're just horsin' around.

419
00:37:39.152 --> 00:37:41.251
Look. I'm begging you. If you do this.

420
00:37:41.252 --> 00:37:42.851
I will lose everything.

421
00:37:42.852 --> 00:37:45.851
There's not a paper in town that will hire me.

422
00:37:45.852 --> 00:37:48.951
You should've thought of that earlier.

423
00:37:48.952 --> 00:37:51.151
What are you doing. Peter?

424
00:37:51.152 --> 00:37:57.402
Show this to the editor. Tell him to check his source next time.

425
00:38:01.751 --> 00:38:03.050
It's a fake!

426
00:38:03.051 --> 00:38:09.701
Empire State Photographic Department confirms it.

427
00:38:10.951 --> 00:38:13.250
Pack your things. Get out of my building.

428
00:38:13.251 --> 00:38:17.150
- I was just...
- You're fired!

429
00:38:17.151 --> 00:38:19.550
You know we're gonna have to print a retraction now.

430
00:38:19.551 --> 00:38:21.250
Haven't printed a retraction in 20 years!

431
00:38:21.251 --> 00:38:27.301
HEADLINE: 
"SORRY SPIDEY Bugle drops charges"

432
00:38:27.751 --> 00:38:29.250
-Shalom?
- Mr Parker?

433
00:38:29.251 --> 00:38:33.050
- Dr Connors here.
- Oh. Dr Connors!

434
00:38:33.051 --> 00:38:34.950
How are you?

435
00:38:34.951 --> 00:38:38.650
Quite a specimen you left me. Parker.

436
00:38:38.651 --> 00:38:46.001
Its chemistry is not unlike the contr*ed meteorites of the 70s.

437
00:38:46.002 --> 00:38:47.002
Thanks. It's good.

438
00:38:46.250 --> 00:38:48.949
You know what. Parker?

439
00:38:48.950 --> 00:38:50.149
Parker?

440
00:38:50.150 --> 00:38:52.749
Give me some milk.

441
00:38:52.750 --> 00:38:56.349
It amplifies characteristics of its host.

442
00:38:56.350 --> 00:38:57.549
Hey. give me another cookie.

443
00:38:57.550 --> 00:39:01.249
Specially aggression.

444
00:39:01.250 --> 00:39:03.049
This can be dangerous.

445
00:39:03.050 --> 00:39:06.349
Peter. you didn't keep any. did you?

446
00:39:06.350 --> 00:39:07.949
You got any with nuts?

447
00:39:07.950 --> 00:39:10.449
Um-- I have some nuts. I could make some.

448
00:39:10.450 --> 00:39:11.749
Go make me some.

449
00:39:11.750 --> 00:39:17.700
- Peter?
- No. no. Of course not.

450
00:39:29.150 --> 00:39:31.449
Your shots are so good.

451
00:39:31.450 --> 00:39:34.648
I'd love to shoot you sometime.

452
00:39:34.649 --> 00:39:38.148
Peter Parker! Peter...

453
00:39:38.149 --> 00:39:39.248
Parker!

454
00:39:39.249 --> 00:39:42.148
Miss Brent. that's not the position I hired you for!

455
00:39:42.149 --> 00:39:45.548
Black suit Spider-Man!

456
00:39:45.549 --> 00:39:48.048
Peter. these are incredible!

457
00:39:48.049 --> 00:39:49.648
We gotta have these. Jonah.

458
00:39:49.649 --> 00:39:52.448
I'll pay you the usual rate.

459
00:39:52.449 --> 00:39:59.499
If you want the shots. I'll take the staff job. Double the money.

460
00:41:30.047 --> 00:41:33.846
You are really gonna dig this joint.

461
00:41:33.847 --> 00:41:35.846
Do you think I'm dressed all right?

462
00:41:35.847 --> 00:41:38.646
Too fancy or...

463
00:41:38.647 --> 00:41:41.946
You're looking fine. babe.

464
00:41:41.947 --> 00:41:43.446
Thank you.

465
00:41:43.447 --> 00:41:47.797
Love that little giggle.

466
00:41:53.446 --> 00:41:57.345
Oh. this is so cool!

467
00:41:57.346 --> 00:42:02.845
I have never been to a jazz club before.

468
00:42:02.846 --> 00:42:08.396
I hope we can get a table.

469
00:42:10.946 --> 00:42:14.545
Find us some shade.

470
00:42:14.546 --> 00:42:16.945
Thanks. ***.

471
00:42:16.946 --> 00:42:21.296
Right this way. sir.

472
00:42:22.646 --> 00:42:26.845
"RESERVED"

473
00:42:26.846 --> 00:42:31.596
Thank you.

474
00:42:34.046 --> 00:42:39.996
- I'm so loving this.
- Oh. me too.

475
00:42:43.445 --> 00:42:45.744
Isn't that your old girlfriend?

476
00:42:45.745 --> 00:42:46.744
Yeah.

477
00:42:46.745 --> 00:42:48.544
Do you want to go someplace else?

478
00:42:48.545 --> 00:42:51.344
No. no. I'll be OK.

479
00:42:51.345 --> 00:42:56.095
Mary Jane. show us what you got.

480
00:43:00.245 --> 00:43:05.595
-I'll be right back.
- Right.

481
00:43:12.345 --> 00:43:16.595
Peter?

482
00:43:16.645 --> 00:43:20.895
This is for you.

483
00:43:24.145 --> 00:43:28.595
Double time!

484
00:43:31.144 --> 00:43:35.194
Thanks.

485
00:43:59.244 --> 00:44:04.094
Now dig all this.

486
00:44:44.343 --> 00:44:49.293
That was all for her?

487
00:44:54.643 --> 00:44:59.193
I'm so sorry.

488
00:45:09.042 --> 00:45:10.141
You all right. Mary Jane?

489
00:45:10.142 --> 00:45:14.592
-I'm fine.
- OK.

490
00:45:14.593 --> 00:45:15.593
Hey.

491
00:45:19.742 --> 00:45:22.441
What's wrong with you?

492
00:45:22.442 --> 00:45:24.241
You.

493
00:45:24.242 --> 00:45:26.041
Can I help you. sir?

494
00:45:26.042 --> 00:45:29.641
-No.
- Is everything OK here. Paul?

495
00:45:29.642 --> 00:45:32.341
Yeah. is everything OK here. Paul?

496
00:45:32.342 --> 00:45:34.541
-Take him out of here.
- Let's go. sir.

497
00:45:34.542 --> 00:45:39.792
Take your hand off me. Now.

498
00:45:43.742 --> 00:45:48.592
Peter. stop!

499
00:45:56.841 --> 00:46:00.540
Who are you?

500
00:46:00.541 --> 00:46:04.891
I don't know.

501
00:47:34.539 --> 00:47:36.738
It's Brock. Sir.

502
00:47:36.739 --> 00:47:40.938
Edward Brock junior.

503
00:47:40.939 --> 00:47:44.938
I come before you today

504
00:47:44.939 --> 00:47:48.338
humbled

505
00:47:48.339 --> 00:47:52.889
and humiliated

506
00:47:53.539 --> 00:47:58.489
to ask you for one thing.

507
00:48:01.339 --> 00:48:06.289
I want you to kill Peter Parker.

508
00:48:53.738 --> 00:48:58.588
Parker?

509
00:50:39.235 --> 00:50:44.134
-Hi. Peter.
- Hi.

510
00:50:44.135 --> 00:50:48.934
You don't seem to have changed the room around very much.

511
00:50:48.935 --> 00:50:52.569
Of course. there's not much you can do.

512
00:50:52.570 --> 00:50:56.685
is there?

513
00:50:59.335 --> 00:51:01.734
When we spoke on the phone.

514
00:51:01.735 --> 00:51:05.034
I sensed something was bothering you.

515
00:51:05.035 --> 00:51:10.085
so I thought I'd just come by.

516
00:51:10.535 --> 00:51:13.334
How's Mary Jane?

517
00:51:13.335 --> 00:51:17.733
I don't know.

518
00:51:17.734 --> 00:51:19.333
I never heard from you.

519
00:51:19.334 --> 00:51:25.184
Did you ever propose?

520
00:51:26.734 --> 00:51:28.433
You said

521
00:51:28.434 --> 00:51:35.384
a husband's gotta put a wife before himself.

522
00:51:38.334 --> 00:51:41.533
I'm not ready.

523
00:51:41.534 --> 00:51:45.233
But what happened?

524
00:51:45.234 --> 00:51:50.084
You seemed so sure.

525
00:51:50.085 --> 00:51:51.085
Yeah. I...

526
00:52:03.034 --> 00:52:07.632
I heard her. Aunt May.

527
00:52:07.633 --> 00:52:11.732
I don't know what to do.

528
00:52:11.733 --> 00:52:16.032
You start by doing the hardest thing.

529
00:52:16.033 --> 00:52:21.183
You forgive yourself.

530
00:52:22.033 --> 00:52:24.832
I believe in you. Peter.

531
00:52:24.833 --> 00:52:28.832
You're a good person.

532
00:52:28.833 --> 00:52:35.883
And I know you will find a way to put it right.

533
00:52:41.333 --> 00:52:45.983
In time.

534
00:53:00.232 --> 00:53:05.982
I don't like Spider-Man.

535
00:53:07.532 --> 00:53:10.531
I want him dead too. Flint.

536
00:53:10.532 --> 00:53:12.931
That's why I've been looking for you.

537
00:53:12.932 --> 00:53:16.431
Oh yeah. I know all about you.

538
00:53:16.432 --> 00:53:18.466
Like the fact that Spider-Man

539
00:53:18.467 --> 00:53:20.831
won't let you help your poor daughter.

540
00:53:20.832 --> 00:53:23.031
It's just-- It doesn't seem right to me.

541
00:53:23.032 --> 00:53:24.331
Look.

542
00:53:24.332 --> 00:53:26.731
I wanna kill the Spider.

543
00:53:26.732 --> 00:53:29.031
You wanna kill the Spider.

544
00:53:29.032 --> 00:53:33.631
Together. he doesn't stand a chance.

545
00:53:33.632 --> 00:53:36.931
Interested?

546
00:53:36.932 --> 00:53:41.281
Yeah.

547
00:54:39.930 --> 00:54:42.829
So--

548
00:54:42.830 --> 00:54:44.329
where to?

549
00:54:44.330 --> 00:54:47.464
"BREAKING NEWS: City in crisis"
- All New York is holding its breath

550
00:54:47.465 --> 00:54:50.629
as a hostage crisis continues to unfold.

551
00:54:50.630 --> 00:54:55.129
Just thirty minutes ago. police came across this startling sight:

552
00:54:55.130 --> 00:54:57.564
A young woman held hostage in a taxi

553
00:54:57.565 --> 00:55:00.229
suspended 80 storeys above the ground

554
00:55:00.230 --> 00:55:03.129
in what appears to be a giant web.

555
00:55:03.130 --> 00:55:06.464
Every attempt by the police to rescue the hostage

556
00:55:06.465 --> 00:55:11.029
has been flaunted by the Sandman.

557
00:55:11.030 --> 00:55:15.528
Compounding the danger is the appearance of a strange black-suited figure.

558
00:55:15.529 --> 00:55:18.128
Early reports had believed him

559
00:55:18.129 --> 00:55:21.163
to be the black-suited Spider-Man. But he is now been identified

560
00:55:21.164 --> 00:55:24.528
as something entirely different.

561
00:55:24.529 --> 00:55:26.528
The hostage has been identified

562
00:55:26.529 --> 00:55:28.528
as Mary Jane Watson.

563
00:55:28.529 --> 00:55:34.579
an actrice recently seen in a brief stint on Broadway.

564
00:55:58.029 --> 00:56:01.727
We're now going to take you live to the scene with Jennifer Dugan.

565
00:56:01.728 --> 00:56:05.127
- Jennifer?
- We're only about 100 feet away now. Hal. and--

566
00:56:05.128 --> 00:56:09.227
Wait. There seems to be some kind of activity in the web.

567
00:56:09.228 --> 00:56:12.327
It seems to be creating some kind of gigantic lettering.

568
00:56:12.328 --> 00:56:15.262
"SPIDER-MAN. STOP US IF YOU CAN"

569
00:56:15.263 --> 00:56:18.527
Apparently. Spider-Man is being challenged to some sort of confrontation.

570
00:56:18.528 --> 00:56:21.127
And that raises serious questions about what kind of chance he'd stand

571
00:56:21.128 --> 00:56:26.778
against such overwhelming...

572
00:56:33.028 --> 00:56:37.678
Harry.

573
00:56:38.928 --> 00:56:40.727
I need your help.

574
00:56:40.728 --> 00:56:46.778
Can't take them both. Not by myself.

575
00:56:51.427 --> 00:56:56.377
You don't deserve my help.

576
00:56:57.027 --> 00:56:59.126
Harry.

577
00:56:59.127 --> 00:57:04.077
she needs us.

578
00:57:05.027 --> 00:57:10.677
Get out.

579
00:57:23.327 --> 00:57:27.126
If I may. Sir.

580
00:57:27.127 --> 00:57:30.126
I've seen things in this house

581
00:57:30.127 --> 00:57:32.126
I've never spoken of.

582
00:57:32.127 --> 00:57:35.325
What are you trying to tell me?

583
00:57:35.326 --> 00:57:38.325
The night your father died

584
00:57:38.326 --> 00:57:42.225
I cleaned his wound.

585
00:57:42.226 --> 00:57:46.025
The blade that pierced his body

586
00:57:46.026 --> 00:57:49.525
came from his glider.

587
00:57:49.526 --> 00:57:51.625
I know

588
00:57:51.626 --> 00:57:53.825
you're trying to defend your father's honor.

589
00:57:53.826 --> 00:57:57.025
but there's no question

590
00:57:57.026 --> 00:58:02.776
that he died by his own hand.

591
00:58:03.126 --> 00:58:06.825
I loved your father.

592
00:58:06.826 --> 00:58:10.425
As I have loved you. Harry.

593
00:58:10.426 --> 00:58:15.876
As your friends love you.

594
00:59:00.025 --> 00:59:04.075
Look!

595
00:59:31.324 --> 00:59:35.223
He seems to have come out of nowhere to 
answer the prayers of the city.

596
00:59:35.224 --> 00:59:41.074
just when all hope seemed to be lost.

597
00:59:43.424 --> 00:59:46.723
Peter?
They're gonna kill us both.

598
00:59:46.724 --> 00:59:48.623
I'm gonna get you out of this.

599
00:59:48.624 --> 00:59:52.874
Watch out!

600
00:59:59.723 --> 01:00:01.122
Hey. Parker.

601
01:00:01.123 --> 01:00:02.622
My God. Eddie?

602
01:00:02.623 --> 01:00:06.622
Oh. my spider-sense is tickling.

603
01:00:06.623 --> 01:00:11.673
If you know what I'm talking about.

604
01:00:28.323 --> 01:00:30.222
We can find a way to settle this.

605
01:00:30.223 --> 01:00:31.822
You're so right.

606
01:00:31.823 --> 01:00:36.122
I'm thinking-- humiliation.

607
01:00:36.123 --> 01:00:39.322
Kinda like you humiliated me.

608
01:00:39.323 --> 01:00:42.921
Do you remember?

609
01:00:42.922 --> 01:00:48.472
Do you remember what you did to me?

610
01:01:01.022 --> 01:01:02.921
You made me lose my girl.

611
01:01:02.922 --> 01:01:06.521
Now I'm gonna make you lose yours.

612
01:01:06.522 --> 01:01:12.372
How's that sound. tiger?

613
01:02:08.321 --> 01:02:13.471
Hold on. Mary Jane!

614
01:02:40.320 --> 01:02:45.070
Mary Jane.

615
01:03:42.719 --> 01:03:46.518
It's hard to believe what's happening.

616
01:03:46.519 --> 01:03:49.017
The brutality of it.

617
01:03:49.018 --> 01:03:51.717
I don't know how he can take any more.

618
01:03:51.718 --> 01:03:53.717
This can be a tragic day

619
01:03:53.718 --> 01:03:55.117
for the people of New York.

620
01:03:55.118 --> 01:04:00.468
It could be the end of Spider-Man.

621
01:04:24.018 --> 01:04:29.168
- Awesome!
- Wicked cool!

622
01:04:51.117 --> 01:04:55.667
You came.

623
01:04:59.517 --> 01:05:02.916
Looks like just in the nick of time.

624
01:05:02.917 --> 01:05:05.616
A couple of minutes ago wouldn't have been so bad either.

625
01:05:05.617 --> 01:05:09.716
What're you gonna do.

626
01:05:09.717 --> 01:05:12.416
I'm needing some help over here.

627
01:05:12.417 --> 01:05:15.916
I'm a little busy right now.

628
01:05:15.917 --> 01:05:20.267
Give me your hand!

629
01:05:32.416 --> 01:05:33.715
Parker!

630
01:05:33.716 --> 01:05:35.015
Parker. where...

631
01:05:35.016 --> 01:05:37.215
I need a photographer!

632
01:05:37.216 --> 01:05:38.815
Hey. kid. You want a job?

633
01:05:38.816 --> 01:05:40.715
Why would I want a job?

634
01:05:40.716 --> 01:05:42.515
I'm just a kid.

635
01:05:42.516 --> 01:05:43.815
All right. how much for the camera?

636
01:05:43.816 --> 01:05:48.515
- One hundred bucks.
- A hundred buck?

637
01:05:48.516 --> 01:05:54.266
All right. you little prick. Here.

638
01:05:57.216 --> 01:06:02.566
Film's extra.

639
01:06:04.316 --> 01:06:08.766
Gotcha.

640
01:06:13.915 --> 01:06:19.265
Pete. watch out!

641
01:06:38.915 --> 01:06:41.549
- You still got any more?
- Hang on!

642
01:06:41.550 --> 01:06:46.065
To what?

643
01:06:47.115 --> 01:06:52.265
- Go. buddy!
- Got her!

644
01:06:59.914 --> 01:07:03.113
You OK?

645
01:07:03.114 --> 01:07:07.013
Yeah.

646
01:07:07.014 --> 01:07:09.513
Good.

647
01:07:09.514 --> 01:07:12.713
Hey. Pete.

648
01:07:12.714 --> 01:07:17.264
Am I interrupting?

649
01:08:29.813 --> 01:08:32.411
Never wound

650
01:08:32.412 --> 01:08:38.262
what you can't kill.

651
01:08:39.312 --> 01:08:42.911
Eddie-- this suit-- you gotta take it off!

652
01:08:42.912 --> 01:08:47.411
Oh. you'd like that. wouldn't you?

653
01:08:47.412 --> 01:08:50.011
I know what it feels like.

654
01:08:50.012 --> 01:08:51.511
It feels good.

655
01:08:51.512 --> 01:08:54.511
The power. Everything.

656
01:08:54.512 --> 01:08:56.811
But you'll lose yourself.

657
01:08:56.812 --> 01:08:58.511
Let it go.

658
01:08:58.512 --> 01:09:02.711
I like being bad.

659
01:09:02.712 --> 01:09:07.562
It makes me happy.

660
01:09:53.711 --> 01:09:58.661
Harry!

661
01:11:08.009 --> 01:11:11.159
Peter. what are you doing?

662
01:11:11.878 --> 01:11:13.198
No!

663
01:11:14.709 --> 01:11:19.059
Eddie!

664
01:11:35.809 --> 01:11:37.508
- Harry?
- Mary Jane.

665
01:11:37.509 --> 01:11:39.007
I'm going to get help.

666
01:11:39.008 --> 01:11:44.458
Stay.

667
01:11:50.508 --> 01:11:55.358
I didn't want this.

668
01:11:57.208 --> 01:12:01.858
But I had no choice.

669
01:12:02.908 --> 01:12:05.207
We always have a choice.

670
01:12:05.208 --> 01:12:08.707
You had a choice when you killed my uncle.

671
01:12:08.708 --> 01:12:13.007
My daughter was dying.

672
01:12:13.008 --> 01:12:18.558
I needed money.

673
01:12:19.708 --> 01:12:24.958
I was scared.

674
01:12:29.407 --> 01:12:32.409
I told your uncle all I wanted was the car.

675
01:12:32.829 --> 01:12:34.970
What is it?
- I need your car.

676
01:12:35.707 --> 01:12:38.506
He said to me:

677
01:12:38.507 --> 01:12:44.457
"Why don't you just put down the gun and go home?"

678
01:12:45.607 --> 01:12:50.857
I realize now he was just trying to help me.

679
01:12:54.807 --> 01:12:58.306
Then I saw my partner running over with the cash.

680
01:12:58.307 --> 01:13:03.357
and the gun was in my hand.

681
01:13:14.506 --> 01:13:18.205
Did a terrible thing to you.

682
01:13:18.206 --> 01:13:23.856
I spent a lot of nights wishing I could take it back.

683
01:13:26.906 --> 01:13:30.405
I'm not asking you to forgive me.

684
01:13:30.406 --> 01:13:35.256
I just want you to understand.

685
01:13:41.806 --> 01:13:47.556
I've done terrible things too.

686
01:14:00.605 --> 01:14:06.955
You didn't choose to be this.

687
01:14:12.305 --> 01:14:16.604
The only thing left to me now

688
01:14:16.605 --> 01:14:21.855
is my daughter.

689
01:14:31.705 --> 01:14:36.455
I forgive you.

690
01:15:16.104 --> 01:15:20.203
Hey. pal. How are you doing?

691
01:15:20.204 --> 01:15:22.203
Been better.

692
01:15:22.204 --> 01:15:27.654
We'll get you through this.

693
01:15:29.004 --> 01:15:33.154
No.

694
01:15:37.303 --> 01:15:41.502
You should never forgive...

695
01:15:41.503 --> 01:15:45.302
...said those things.

696
01:15:45.303 --> 01:15:50.602
None of that matters. Peter.

697
01:15:50.603 --> 01:15:55.153
You're my friend.

698
01:15:56.803 --> 01:16:02.053
Best friend.

699
01:17:04.902 --> 01:17:08.800
<i>"Whatever comes our way."</i>

700
01:17:08.801 --> 01:17:15.151
<i>"Whatever battle we have raging inside us. 
we always have a choice."</i>

701
01:17:15.201 --> 01:17:17.600
<i>"My friend Harry taught me that."</i>

702
01:17:17.601 --> 01:17:21.500
<i>"He chose to be the best of himself."</i>

703
01:17:21.501 --> 01:17:24.600
<i>"It's the choices that make us who we are."</i>

704
01:17:24.601 --> 01:17:30.451
<i>"and we can always choose to do what's right."</i>

705
01:17:31.800 --> 01:17:35.700
[Music Begins]

706
01:17:35.701 --> 01:17:39.400
<i> I'm through with love... </i>

707
01:17:39.401 --> 01:17:42.400
<i>  I'll never fall again ...</i>

708
01:17:42.401 --> 01:17:45.900
<i>  Said adieu to love ...</i>

709
01:17:45.901 --> 01:17:49.300
<i>Don't ever call again... </i>

710
01:17:49.301 --> 01:17:52.400
<i> For I must have you...</i>

711
01:17:52.401 --> 01:17:56.399
<i> Or no one...</i>

712
01:17:56.400 --> 01:18:02.299
<i> And so I'm through with love... </i>

713
01:18:02.300 --> 01:18:05.199
<i> I've locked my heart...</i>

714
01:18:05.200 --> 01:18:08.399
<i> I'll keep my feelings there...</i>

715
01:18:08.400 --> 01:18:11.599
<i>  I have stocked my heart...</i>

716
01:18:11.600 --> 01:18:14.599
<i> With icy frigid air...</i>

717
01:18:14.600 --> 01:18:17.699
<i> And I mean to care...</i>

718
01:18:17.700 --> 01:18:23.050
<i> For no one...</i>

719
01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:35.000
~The End~
